## Release-based single-editor concurrency + Close button

### Context

The single-editor edit lock for DRAFT versions used a heartbeat + 90s TTL:
the editor's browser beat every 30s and a lock went "stale" (reclaimable by
anyone) once two beats were missed, with a best-effort release on tab close.
In a multi-page app every navigation is a full unload, so the lock was
released-and-reacquired on every page change, and the TTL made ownership
fuzzy. The requested model is simpler and explicit: once a user opens a DRAFT
domain in edit mode, everyone else is view-only **until that user explicitly
closes the domain** (or an admin takes over). No timeouts.

### Changes

1. `src/back/objects/registry/store/lakebase/store.py`
   - `acquire_edit_lock`: removed the TTL/stale reclamation clause — a lock
     held by another user is never taken implicitly (only free / same holder
     / `force` grant it). Dropped `_EDIT_LOCK_TTL_S`.
   - Removed `heartbeat_edit_lock` entirely.
   - `_get_edit_lock_row` / `_edit_lock_row_to_dict`: dropped the computed
     `stale` field and the `heartbeat_at` read. The `heartbeat_at` column is
     retained (unused) to avoid a destructive migration on live registries.

2. `src/back/objects/registry/EditLockService.py`
   - Removed `heartbeat()`; dropped all `stale` handling from `blocking_holder`,
     `_shape`, and `_none`. Rewrote the module docstring for the no-TTL model.

3. `src/api/routers/internal/domain.py`
   - Removed the `POST /domain/edit-lock/heartbeat` endpoint.
   - Added `POST /domain/close` — releases the caller's edit lock (what frees
     the version for the next editor), then resets the session. Release runs
     before reset since the lock target is read from the session.

4. `src/shared/fastapi/main.py`
   - Added `/domain/close` to `_DOMAIN_SCOPED_EXCEPTIONS` so any user (viewers
     included) can close the domain they have open. Tidied a docstring.

5. `src/back/objects/domain/Domain.py`
   - Save-to-UC lock re-check simplified from `lock and not lock.get("stale")`
     to `if lock:` (no stale concept).

6. `src/front/static/global/js/edit-lock.js`
   - Removed the heartbeat loop and the tab-close/navigation release (which
     would briefly free the lock mid-session). Keeps the viewer banner and the
     admin "Take over editing" action. Rewrote the header comment.

7. `src/front/config/menu_config.json`
   - Renamed the `Save Domain` action label to `Save`; added a `Close` action
     (`domainClose`, `#menuCloseDomain`).

8. `src/front/templates/base.html`
   - Render the `Close` button beside `Save` in the L2 subnav.

9. `src/front/static/global/js/base-ui-handlers.js`
   - Whitelisted `domainClose` for `data-navbar-action` dispatch.

10. `src/front/static/global/js/navbar.js`
    - Added `domainClose()` + a "Save before closing?" dialog (Save & Close /
      Close without saving / Cancel) and `closeDomainSession()` (POST
      `/domain/close` then redirect to Home). `doDomainSave()` now returns a
      success boolean so Save & Close can abort on failure.

11. `src/front/static/global/css/main.css`
    - Added `.ob-subnav-close-btn` styling (danger-tinted hover).

12. `src/back/objects/registry/store/lakebase/schema.sql`
    - Updated the `domain_edit_locks` comment (no TTL/heartbeat; held until
      explicit close / take-over / status change).

13. Tests
    - `tests/units/registry/test_edit_lock_store.py`: dropped heartbeat/TTL/
      stale assertions; asserts the upsert has no `make_interval` clause.
    - `tests/units/registry/test_edit_lock_service.py`: removed heartbeat and
      stale-based tests.
    - `tests/units/api/test_edit_lock_endpoints.py`: removed the heartbeat
      test; added a `/domain/close` delegation test.
    - `tests/units/domain/test_change_audit.py`: `_svc()` mock now returns no
      edit lock (`get_edit_lock -> None`), matching the free-lock default.

14. Documentation
    - `docs/user-guide.md`: new "Single-editor concurrency (open in edit vs.
      view) & the Close button" subsection; `Save Domain` → `Save`/`Close`
      wording.
    - `docs/architecture.md`: documented the release-based single-editor lock
      in the `PermissionMiddleware` lifecycle-gate note.
    - `docs/features.md`: added a "Single-editor concurrency" feature bullet.
    - `README.md`: added a "Single-editor concurrency" bullet.
    - `releases/ReleaseNotes_V0.6.0.md`: rewrote the Domain Edit-Lock section
      for the release-based model + Close button; updated summary and file map.
    - Sphinx guides `{include}` these source `.md` files, so the changes flow
      into the HTML docs on the next `docs` build.

