## Deploy: re-pin `uv.lock` to the public CDN + redeploy v0.6.0

### Context

A `make deploy` pre-flight caught that the committed `uv.lock` (HEAD `e636189`,
the "release previous domain's edit-lock" commit) had every URL rewritten back
to `pypi-proxy.dev.databricks.com` (3994 proxied lines) — accidental churn from
running `uv` in the proxied dev shell during that unrelated feature commit. The
Apps container runs `uv run --frozen`, and the internal proxy cold-caches fresh
wheels and times out, which crashes the deploy. The lock had last been correctly
pinned to the public CDN in `d9cf05a`; the two dev-only deps added afterward
(`pytest-html`, `pytest-dependency`) meant a wholesale revert to `d9cf05a` was
not safe (it would drop them and break `--frozen`'s lock↔pyproject consistency).

### Changes

1. `uv.lock`
   - Host-swapped both proxied URL forms back to the public CDN, preserving
     HEAD's full dependency set (incl. the two new dev deps): every
     `https://pypi-proxy.dev.databricks.com/packages/…` wheel/sdist URL →
     `https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/…` (identical paths + hashes,
     verified against `d9cf05a`), and every
     `registry = "https://pypi-proxy.dev.databricks.com/simple"` →
     `registry = "https://pypi.org/simple"`. 3994 lines total (3658 file URLs +
     336 registry lines). Confirmed 0 proxy references remain; only
     `files.pythonhosted.org` (3658) and `pypi.org` (336) hosts; content diff vs
     HEAD (ignoring URL/registry lines) is empty.

### Modified files

- `uv.lock`

### Test result

- Lockfile in sync: `UV_INDEX_URL=https://pypi.org/simple uv lock --check` → exit 0.
- `uv run --frozen pytest -q -m "not scenario"` → **2948 passed, 275 skipped, 0
  failed** in ~20s.
- `make deploy` → both apps bootstrapped (`ontobricks-060`, `mcp-ontobricks-060`),
  app-perms + Lakebase schema/permissions applied. App status `RUNNING` /
  compute `ACTIVE` ("App started successfully"); `/healthz` → **HTTP 200** at
  `https://ontobricks-060-2508734981122804.aws.databricksapps.com`.
